implements ExtensionPoint
    NOTE: ALL TableRowMapper CLASSES MUST END IN "TableRowMapper". If not, the ClassSearcher will not find them. An interface that allows implementors to map an object of one type to another. This is useful for table models that have row types that are easily converted to other more generic types.

    This interface is an ExtensionPoint so that once created, they will be ingested automatically by Ghidra. Once discovered, these mappers will be used to provide dynamic columns to to tables with row types that match ROW_TYPE.

    See Also:
    DynamicTableColumn, TableUtils
